comments.body:
@SteveL-MSFT 

Apologies!!  Yes! It's happening in DOS Command Prompt too. But, is not happening with WSL Ubuntu prompt.

FYI - I'm using VMware Workstation to create my VM's.  I got one non-Insider version that's working fine.

@SteveL-MSFT 

In my case, I discovered that my issue is leaning towards VMWare Tools on my VM. I get the cursor back if I remove VMWare Tool from Windows 10 17677.

I posted the issue in UserVoice: https://windowsserver.uservoice.com/forums/295047-general-feedback/suggestions/34422874-windows-server-insider-17677-all-shells-lost-con
